criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:

          -  25 - 70 years old;

          -  mean daytime systolic BP> 130 mm. Hg.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Severe or end-stage organ disease (liver, kidney, heart, lung) or history of diabetic
             ketoacidosis, or any other illness with expected survival less than 1 year;

          -  severe cognitive impairment;

          -  diagnosed psychiatric illness or disability;

          -  clinical significant cardiac arrhythmia;

          -  symptomatic orthostatic hypertension;

          -  pregnancy;

          -  not fluent in english.
